    "Others approach Markowitz's method from the perspective of optimization and control in engineering.",
    "Control systems engineering has a long history and is widely applied in essentially all engineering applications.",
    "Most applications of control engineering use methods based on models that are either wrong or heavily simplified.",
    "While naïve implementations of these methods do not work well (or worse), simple sensible modifications, similar to the ones we describe later in this paper, work very well in practice.",
    "These different backgrounds together can provide a new perspective and bring modern tools to the endeavor Markowitz began."
